Johannesburg- Amapiano vocalist Sir Trill has recently shared that he wants to give his royalties from his latest project to Mpura’s family, where he featured the late star. Sir Trill was set to release his latest offering at the end of last year but due to certain circumstances, he did not. Taking to social media he explained to his fans why he ended up not releasing his latest offering that he was working on.  Mpura and Killer Kau passed away last year the two died in a car accident, while they were on their way to a gig in Rustenburg. Also Read: Mpura and Killer Kau have passed away For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here